  "title": "Marine Logistics Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate with Managers and Superintendents to ensure timely supply of technical spare parts, vessel repair jobs, and annual service requirements.</li>\n  <li>Manage purchasing activities, including raising purchase orders, arranging logistics, and ensuring smooth delivery of spares to vessels.</li>\n  <li>Handle enquiries and requisitions from suppliers, obtain quotations, and prepare relevant shipping and billing documents such as proforma invoices, packing lists, and delivery orders.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with vessels to clarify requisition details and ensure accuracy of supply.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with agents and vendors to coordinate shipment of spare parts or repair services at suitable ports.</li>\n  <li>Support documentation, invoice verification, and cost approval processes before submission to accounts.</li>\n  <li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by Managers or Superintendents.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or equivalent qualification.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 6 months to 1 year of experience, preferably in the shipping or marine repair industry.</li>\n  <li>Good communication, coordination, and organizational skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
